01:02:39,671 --> 01:02:40,753
Rym: But you generally should.

1125
01:02:40,793 --> 01:02:47,850
Rym: if you make a commitment, you should stick to that commitment or don't make the commitment in the first place or be honest about it.

1126
01:02:48,111 --> 01:02:51,090
Rym: Like if Scott invited that con and I was like and maybe I don't bail yet.

1127
01:02:51,210 --> 01:02:52,089
Rym: Maybe I don't say no.

1128
01:02:52,631 --> 01:02:56,359
Rym: Maybe I say I'm not sure I need to decide.

1129
01:02:56,800 --> 01:03:00,790
Rym: when do I need to make the decision by those.

1130
01:03:00,851 --> 01:03:02,350
Rym: Those are the conversations to have.

1131
01:03:02,910 --> 01:03:03,191
Rym: We have.

1132
01:03:03,291 --> 01:03:09,808
Rym: I've gone to cons that I would have bailed on, but I'd signed a contract to go to that one car that we signed a contract to go to.

1133
01:03:10,148 --> 01:03:10,710
Scott: that we could have.

1134
01:03:11,373 --> 01:03:13,150
Rym: We could have bailed out if we'd known in advance.

1135
01:03:13,911 --> 01:03:18,570
Scott: There are definitely things where you cross a line of no return.

1136
01:03:18,931 --> 01:03:19,212
Scott: Right.

1137
01:03:19,433 --> 01:03:23,130
Scott: And there is sometimes there's a return with it with a valid reason.

1138
01:03:24,093 --> 01:03:25,770
Rym: Well, like, hey, I'm going to come to your wedding.

1139
